Neil Warnock has tipped Brendan Rodgers to leave Leicester City to take charge of Manchester United in the summer. The Red Devils will be on the lookout for a permanent manager at the end of the season with Ralf Rangnick taking interim charge until the summer. Rodgers is said to be ‘under consideration’ by Man United but former Tottenham manager Mauricio Pochettino remains the favourite to take on the role. Ralf Rangnick Admits Jadon Sancho Snub Before Man Utd Transfer Juventus Youngster Receives Request For Immediate Transfer The Argentinian is currently manager of Ligue 1 giants Paris Saint Germain but is open to leaving the club in the summer. However, Warnock has advised the manager against making the move, instead backing Rodgers to switch clubs.